metadata.name: NOT MY KING
metadata.description:
This piece was made on the morning of the Queens burial. After 2 weeks of news blackout and national mourning I woke up that bank holiday morning with an unmistakable feeling of anger towards our supposed new monarch. As a 2nd generation immigrant I could not shake the feeling that simply accepting this change was an insult to the generations affected by this cantankerous regime and they would only roll in their graves. This was the result.

16.5" x 23.4" @ 300 DPI
